# UI Standards — BCB BizHub

## Design System Primitives

Always use the project's design-system components. **Never** build raw HTML inputs or custom buttons from scratch.

| Need | Use |
|---|---|
| Text input | `<FloatingTextField />` from `@/components/ui/FloatingTextField` |
| Select / dropdown | `<FloatingReactSelect />` from `@/components/ui/FloatingReactSelect` |
| Date picker | `<FloatingDatePicker />` from `@/components/ui/FloatingDatePicker` |
| Textarea | `<FloatingTextArea />` from `@/components/ui/FloatingTextArea` |
| Button | `<Button />` from `@/components/ui/button` (shadcn variant) |
| Dialog / modal | `<Dialog />` from `@/components/ui/dialog` (Radix) |
| Checkbox | `@radix-ui/react-checkbox` via `@/components/ui/checkbox` |
| Radio | `@radix-ui/react-radio-group` via `@/components/ui/radio-group` |
| Progress | `@/components/ui/progress` |

## Brand Colour Tokens (Tailwind)

Only use CSS custom property tokens — never hardcode hex values.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — uses design tokens
<div className="bg-primary text-primary-foreground">
<div className="text-neutral-700 border-neutral-300">
<div className="bg-neutral-100 text-neutral-900">

// ❌ BAD — hardcoded colours
<div style={{ backgroundColor: '#002060' }}>
<div className="text-[#697786]">
```

Standard Bank brand scale:
- `primary` / `primary-light` / `primary-medium` / `primary-dark` / `primary-deep`
- `neutral-100` through `neutral-950` (see tailwind.config.js)
- `destructive` for errors · `muted` for secondary text

## Typography

Font family is `BentonSansPro` — available via Tailwind as `font-bspro` or via `var(--font-bspro)`.

```tsx
// ✅ Headings
<h1 className="text-2xl font-semibold text-neutral-900 font-bspro">
// ✅ Body
<p className="text-sm text-neutral-700">
// ✅ Labels / captions
<span className="text-xs text-neutral-500">
```

## Component Patterns

### Functional components with explicit prop interfaces
```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
interface BusinessCardProps {
  tradingName: string;
  registrationNumber: string;
  isActive?: boolean;
}

export function BusinessCard({ tradingName, registrationNumber, isActive = false }: BusinessCardProps) {
  return (...)
}

// ❌ BAD — implicit props, default export only file
export default function ({ data }: any) { ... }
```

### Client vs Server Components
- Default to **Server Components** (no `'use client'`)
- Add `'use client'` **only** when using: `useState`, `useEffect`, event handlers, browser APIs, Zustand stores
- Data-fetching components are Server Components — pass data down as props

### CSS Modules for component-scoped styles
- Component-specific animation or complex selectors → use `.module.css` co-located with the component
- Utility/layout classes → Tailwind directly in JSX
- **Never** use inline `style={{}}` except for dynamic computed values (e.g., chart percentages)

## Accessibility Requirements (banking-grade)

Every interactive element must meet WCAG 2.1 AA:

```tsx
// ✅ Form fields
<FloatingTextField
  label="ID Number"
  aria-required="true"
  aria-describedby="id-helper"
  errorText="Please enter a valid 13-digit SA ID number"
/>

// ✅ Icon buttons must have visible label or aria-label
<button aria-label="Close dialog" onClick={onClose}>
  <X className="h-4 w-4" />
</button>

// ✅ Alerts / status messages
<div role="alert" aria-live="assertive" className="text-destructive text-sm">
  {error}
</div>

// ❌ BAD — missing label
<input type="text" placeholder="Enter ID" />
```

## Loading & Error States

Every async-backed component must render all three states:

```tsx
if (isLoading) return <LoadingSkeleton />   // use Tailwind animate-pulse skeleton
if (error) return <ErrorBanner message={error} />
return <ActualContent data={data} />
```

## Responsive Layout

- Mobile-first: start with base styles, add `md:` / `lg:` breakpoints
- Banking forms: single column on mobile (`flex flex-col gap-4`), two-column on desktop (`md:grid md:grid-cols-2 md:gap-6`)
- Touch targets: minimum `h-11` (44px) for all interactive elements

## Prohibited Patterns

- No `any` type in component props
- No `console.log` left in production code
- No hardcoded strings for user-facing copy — use a constants file or i18n key
- No business logic (API calls, calculations) inside JSX return statements
- No direct `fetch()` calls inside React components — use stores or Server Components
